cs.IT, cs.SP, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the problem of detecting the sparsity pattern of a vector from noisy measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the performance of various algorithms for sparsity pattern recovery, which falls under the category of machine learning and statistics. Hence, cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which suggests the categories cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Systems and Control) as possible categories.
